.TH "pcd-lint" "1" "April 2026" "pcd-lint 0.3.21" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
pcd-lint \[em] Post-Coding Development specification linter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]pcd-lint\f[R] [\f[I]strict=true\f[R]] \f[I]specfile.md\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]pcd-lint\f[R] \f[B]list-templates\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]pcd-lint\f[R] \f[B]version\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]pcd-lint\f[R] validates Post-Coding Development (PCD) specification
files against the structural rules defined in the PCD spec schema
(v0.3.21).
.PP
It checks required sections, META fields, SPDX license identifiers,
BEHAVIOR blocks, EXAMPLES structure, INVARIANTS tags, MILESTONE
sections, and more.
All rules are evaluated \[em] linting does not stop at the first error.
.PP
Diagnostics are written to \f[B]stderr\f[R].
The summary line is written to \f[B]stdout\f[R].
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\f[B]list-templates\f[R]
Print all known deployment templates with their default language
annotation.
Outputs exactly 17 lines.
Exits 0.
.TP
\f[B]version\f[R]
Print pcd-lint version, spec-schema version, and embedded SPDX list
version.
Format:
\f[V]pcd-lint {version} (schema {spec-schema}) spdx/{spdx-version}\f[R]
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]strict=true\f[R]
Treat warnings as errors.
Exit code 1 if any warning is present.
Default: strict=false.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Valid specification.
No errors; no warnings (or strict=false and only warnings).
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
Invalid specification.
At least one error; or strict=true and at least one warning.
.TP
\f[B]2\f[R]
Invocation error.
Bad arguments, file not found, or unreadable file.
.SH OUTPUT STREAMS
.PP
Diagnostics (errors and warnings) are written to \f[B]stderr\f[R].
.PP
The summary line and list-templates output are written to
\f[B]stdout\f[R].
.SH DIAGNOSTIC FORMAT
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
{SEVERITY}  {file}:{line}  [{section}]  {message}
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Examples:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
ERROR    spec.md:1    [structure]  Missing required section: ## INVARIANTS
ERROR    spec.md:4    [META]       Missing required META field: Deployment
WARNING  spec.md:6    [META]       META field \[aq]Target\[aq] is deprecated since v0.3.0
\f[R]
.fi
.SH SUMMARY FORMAT
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
\[OK] spec.md: valid
\[OK] spec.md: valid (N warning(s))
\[u2717] spec.md: N error(s), M warning(s)
\[u2717] spec.md: N error(s), M warning(s) [strict mode]
\f[R]
.fi
.SH INVOCATION EXAMPLES
.PP
Lint a specification file:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
pcd-lint mycomponent.md
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Lint with strict mode (warnings treated as errors):
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
pcd-lint strict=true mycomponent.md
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
List all known deployment templates:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
pcd-lint list-templates
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Print version information:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
pcd-lint version
\f[R]
.fi
.SH TEMPLATE SEARCH PATH
.PP
Template files are searched in the following directories (ascending
precedence):
.IP "1." 3
\f[V]/usr/share/pcd/templates/\f[R] \[em] vendor default (pcd-templates
package)
.IP "2." 3
\f[V]/etc/pcd/templates/\f[R] \[em] system administrator additions
.IP "3." 3
\f[V]\[ti]/.config/pcd/templates/\f[R] \[em] user additions
.IP "4." 3
\f[V]./.pcd/templates/\f[R] \[em] project-local
.PP
Directories that do not exist are silently skipped.
.SH VALIDATION RULES
.PP
\f[B]RULE-01\f[R]: Required sections present (META, TYPES, BEHAVIOR,
PRECONDITIONS, POSTCONDITIONS, INVARIANTS, EXAMPLES).
.PP
\f[B]RULE-02\f[R]: META fields present and non-empty (Deployment,
Verification, Safety-Level, Version, Spec-Schema, License, Author).
.PP
\f[B]RULE-02c/02d\f[R]: Version and Spec-Schema must match
MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH.
.PP
\f[B]RULE-02e\f[R]: License must be a valid SPDX identifier or compound
expression.
.PP
\f[B]RULE-03\f[R]: Deployment value must be a known deployment template.
.PP
\f[B]RULE-04\f[R]: Deprecated META fields (Target, Domain) emit
warnings.
.PP
\f[B]RULE-05\f[R]: Verification field must be one of: none, lean4,
fstar, dafny, custom.
.PP
\f[B]RULE-06/07\f[R]: EXAMPLES section must contain complete
EXAMPLE/GIVEN/WHEN/THEN blocks.
.PP
\f[B]RULE-08\f[R]: Every BEHAVIOR block must contain a STEPS: block.
.PP
\f[B]RULE-09\f[R]: INVARIANTS entries should carry [observable] or
[implementation] tags.
.PP
\f[B]RULE-10\f[R]: BEHAVIOR blocks with error exits must have a
negative-path EXAMPLE.
.PP
\f[B]RULE-13\f[R]: Constraint: field on BEHAVIOR headers must be
required, supported, or forbidden.
.PP
\f[B]RULE-14\f[R]: Deployment templates must have an EXECUTION section.
.PP
\f[B]RULE-15/16/17\f[R]: MILESTONE sections are validated for structure,
status, and BEHAVIOR name existence.
.SH INSTALLATION
.PP
\f[B]pcd-lint\f[R] is distributed via OBS (build.opensuse.org) as part
of the \f[B]pcd-tools\f[R] package.
.PP
\f[B]openSUSE / SUSE Linux Enterprise:\f[R]
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
zypper install pcd-tools
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
\f[B]Fedora:\f[R]
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
dnf install pcd-tools
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
\f[B]Debian / Ubuntu:\f[R]
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
apt install pcd-tools
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
The \f[B]pcd-templates\f[R] package is required and provides template
files to \f[V]/usr/share/pcd/templates/\f[R].
.PP
No curl-based installation is supported.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[V]/usr/share/pcd/templates/\f[R]
Vendor-default template files (provided by pcd-templates package).
.TP
\f[V]/etc/pcd/templates/\f[R]
System administrator template additions.
.TP
\f[V]\[ti]/.config/pcd/templates/\f[R]
User template additions.
.TP
\f[V]./.pcd/templates/\f[R]
Project-local template overrides.
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
The PCD specification schema documentation is available at the project
repository.
Template files follow the naming convention
\f[V]{name}.template.md\f[R].
